message:
Fix tooling, move configs, maintain previous settings

- Add previously omitted tooling, maintain previous settings to Pipfile
- Move configs (pyproject.toml + .flake8 instead of pyproject.toml +
  setup.cfg) for better compatability with
  https://opensource.creativecommons.org/contributing-code/python-guidelines/
- Revert to previous tooling settings to minimize delta
updated pre-commit to use pipenv and improved check behavior
reorganize dev info and replace manual check with pre-commit install

Update code, settings, and docs for main default branch

- Update to reflect main is now configured as default branch (here and
  in cc-licenses-data
- licenses/tests/test_git_utils.py
  - Also update variable names and comments to increase clarity

Added step by step instructions to set up project developement environemnt on linux based systems
So it becoms easier for new contributors to start working on the project

Modified the documentation on the README.md file, for better clarity on setting up the
project developement environment on linux based systems
update documentation to reflect new legacy data location (cc-licenses-data/blob/main/legacy)
Extend docker documentation and add static docker setup
rename primary docker container to app and improve docs
update load_html_files command with default input_directory and add error if the input_directory does not exist (or is not a directory)
namespace update: use unit instead of license_code. reset django migrations

Increase "Legal Code" clarity

Previously the codebase used three different terms to refer to the same
thing:
1. "legal code"
2. "legalcode"
3. "license"

With this update, "legal code" is used nearly exclusively. The only exceptions
are established paths.
add dependency documentation and correct formatting
improve translation organization and add doc references
update url for Transifex CC public page
clarify django translation domain / transifex resource. clean-up and reorganization
replace bad partially duplicated info with reference

improve translation documentation and use docker-compose exec

- use `docker-compose exec` instead of `docker-compose run` (there is no
  need to spawn a new container which then requires cleanup)
- add language codes documentation per #157
- clarify django translation domain per #163 and #164
add additional clarity to language codes

update readme

- add Licenses and Public Domain Declarations section
- reorganize sections at top to prioritize key information before
  development information
- add references to custom domains and language code subdirectories
- correct spelling errors
increase clarity & consistency of translation file description
translation details were moved to data repo
add Helper Scripts section to README
add instructions to install Docker Compose
use title case for entire label
repository renames and application renames. includes database migration reset
update to Python 3.9 and run coverage in parallel
remove specific versions where links to latest
update ports so they no longer conflict with creativecommons/project_creativecommons.org docker services
docker compose is now part of docker
use "dedication" instead of "declaration" for cc0 and public domain tools, in general
use less specific terms when a variety of tools are referenced
Add windows specific notes checks validate
Add windows specific notes checks validate
Add windows specific notes changes made

Grammatical Mistakes Fixed in Readme

Fixed typos and Grammatical mistakes in the Readme file.
update and clarify documentation and licensing
update formatting of notice and warning
remove unnecessary commentary on running app as a service
